The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, February 03, 2004 				 Fair row over flag
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Feb. 2: Students who pointed out a national flag hoisted wrong side up at a stall in the book fair were allegedly abused and assaulted this evening.																								The students, who claimed to be SFI members, alleged that volunteers and security personnel tore it up when they demanded that the flag be hoisted properly. 																								Outnumbered in the war of words, they organised a sit-in outside the stall and lodged a complaint at Maidan police station.
